  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Israel Terminally Ill Law, 2005 allows patients who are terminally ill and ventilated to
      have their ventilator placed on a timer which at a specific time in the future stops the
      ventilator, maintains the patient on positive pressure (CPAP) and allows the patient not to
      be reconnected to the ventilator. We will evaluate the safety of the Automatic Respiration
      Transfer-Timer by assessing vital signs, oxygenation and ventilatory pressures and volumes
      during the use of the timer with the regular ventilator. In addition, we will evaluate
      whether the timer stops the ventilator and switches to CPAP at the designated time.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
